163 0 obj
  << /ActualText (From there\054 we 3D\055printed models of various brains to gain a clear visual understanding of which differed most strikingly from the human brain\024and thus offered the most compelling comparisons\056 \n\n\n\nThroughout this process\054 we maintained focus on the core themes of intelligence\054 environment\054 evolution\054 and emotions\056\n\n\n\nTo identify each species\047 predominant qualities\054 we created mind maps grouping those with shared characteristics\056 This revealed that ants\054 birds\054 elephants\054 and octopuses had the most visually distinctive brains for comparison against humans\056 \n\n\n\nThe next step was verifying whether these species also demonstrated brain\055related abilities that made them meaningful subjects for deeper exploration\056)
     /K [ 3 ]
     /P 164 0 R
     /Pg 160 0 R
     /S /Span
     /Type /StructElem
  >>
endobj

